WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.100
CHAPTER X.

00:09.740 --> 00:16.400
THE PROVERBS OF SOLOMON A wise son maketh a glad father.

00:17.000 --> 00:20.340
But a foolish son is the heaviness of his mother.

00:21.420 --> 00:26.580
Treasures of wickedness profit nothing, But righteousness delivereth from death.

00:27.160 --> 00:30.920
The Lord will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish,

00:31.180 --> 00:34.100
But he casteth away the substance of the wicked.

00:35.300 --> 00:38.740
He becomeeth poor that dealeth with a slack hand,

00:39.480 --> 00:41.940
But the hand of the diligent maketh rich.

00:43.260 --> 00:46.020
He that gathereth in summer is a wise son,

00:46.780 --> 00:50.880
But he that sleepeth in harvest is a son that causeth shame.

00:51.800 --> 00:57.380
Blessings are upon the head of the just, But violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.

00:58.820 --> 01:05.280
The memory of the just is blessed, But the name of the wicked shall rot.

01:06.220 --> 01:12.200
The wise in heart will receive commandments, But a prating fool shall fall.

01:13.180 --> 01:20.440
He that walketh uprightly walketh surely, But he that perverteth his ways shall be known.

01:20.880 --> 01:27.480
He that winketh with the eye causeth sorrow, But a prating fool shall fall.

01:28.300 --> 01:35.340
The mouth of a righteous man is a well of life, But violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.

01:36.380 --> 01:42.580
Hatred stirreth up strifes, But love covereth all sins.

01:43.500 --> 01:47.080
In the lips of him that hath understanding wisdom is found,

01:47.800 --> 01:51.800
But a rod is for the back of him that is void of understanding.

01:53.180 --> 01:58.520
Wise men lay up knowledge, But the mouth of the foolish is near destruction.

01:59.140 --> 02:05.920
The rich man's wealth is his strong city, The destruction of the poor is their poverty.

02:06.520 --> 02:11.740
The labor of the righteous tendeth to life, The fruit of the wicked to sin.

02:12.280 --> 02:18.400
He is in the way of life that keepeth instruction, But he that refuseth reproof ereth.

02:19.520 --> 02:25.320
He that hideeth hatred with lying lips, And he that uttereth a slander is a fool.

02:26.460 --> 02:33.400
In the multitude of words there wanteth not sin, But he that refraineth his lips is wise.

02:34.140 --> 02:40.980
The tongue of the just is as choice silver, The heart of the wicked is little worth.

02:41.740 --> 02:47.080
The lips of the righteous feed many, But fools die for want of wisdom.

02:48.800 --> 02:54.060
The blessing of the Lord it maketh rich, And he addeth no sorrow with it.

02:54.960 --> 03:00.880
It is as sport to a fool to do mischief, But a man of understanding hath wisdom.

03:02.320 --> 03:08.060
The fear of the wicked it shall come upon him, But the desire of the righteous shall be granted.

03:08.780 --> 03:17.020
As the whirlwind passeth, so is the wicked no more, But the righteous is an everlasting foundation.

03:18.100 --> 03:25.760
As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, So is the sluggard to them that send him.

03:27.760 --> 03:33.740
The fear of the Lord prolongeth days, But the years of the wicked shall be shortened.

03:35.360 --> 03:41.740
The hope of the righteous shall be gladness, But the expectation of the wicked shall perish.

03:43.700 --> 03:50.220
The way of the Lord is strength to the upright, But destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.

03:51.300 --> 03:56.300
The righteous shall never be removed, But the wicked shall not inhabit the earth.

03:57.360 --> 04:03.720
The mouth of the just bringeth forth wisdom, But the foward tongue shall be cut out.

04:05.280 --> 04:12.180
The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable, But the mouth of the wicked speaketh fowardness.

